        Nonpositive or missing weights are treated as 0.0. If every weight ends
        up being zero (or self.tip_weights is empty), falls back to a uniform
        draw over TIPS via self.rng.choice(). Uses self.rng for both the
        cumulative-distribution threshold and the uniform fallback, so
        selection stays deterministic for a fixed seed.
